Git is a version controlling and collabrotaion system which help to save checkpoints in software.
git is just a software 
github is a online git versioning services provider.
version track file for changes save and mark chekcpoint and back to ther and working with collabrotaive environment 
repo it is short from of repository(folder)
get init git will intilaize .git file 
logs is stores haases of previous commit 

 Write > Add > Commit 

..git commands..
find version      -- git --version  
check status      -- git status 
git intilaize     -- git init  
git adding file   -- git add file_name 
all file adding   -- git add .
adding and commit -- git commit -am "update and commmit"
for unstage files -- git rm --cached file_name
git branch        -- git branch -m main
git add remote    -- git remote add origin {Link of repo}
git remove remote -- git remote remove origin 
check checkpoints -- git log
in one line log   -- git log --oneline 
push on github    -- git push -u origin main

forcefully push   -- git push origin main --force
remember username -- git config --global user.name "sinzq"
remember email    -- git config --global user.email "shivam.singh8@yahoo.com"
checke user name  -- git config --global user.name
checek user mail  -- git config --global user.email 
in one line       -- git config --global --list



